.TH GUESSNUM(1),User Commands,GUESSNUM(1)

.SH NAME
guessnum - guess the number game

.SH SYNOPSIS
guessnum

.SH DESCRIPTION
guessnum picks a random number between 1 and 100 and asks you to guess it.
After each guess it tells you whether your guess was too low, too high, or correct.
When you guess correctly, it reports how many guesses you needed and asks if you want to play again.

.SH EXAMPLES
Start a game:

$ guessnum
Guess #1: 50
Too low!
Guess #2: 75
Too high!
Guess #3: 62
Correct! Number of guesses: 3
Play again (y/n)?

.SH EXIT STATUS
guessnum exits 0 when the player chooses not to play again.
